
@startuml
skinparam monochrome true
skinparam noteAlign center

class Employee {
  - name: String
  - socialSecurityNumber: String
}

class CreativeEmployee {
  + isOscarWinner: Boolean
}

class Director extends CreativeEmployee {
  - assistantName: String
}

class Actor extends CreativeEmployee {
  - education: String
}

class Technician {
  - fieldOfActivity: String
}

class FilmSet {
  - location: String
  - films: List<Film>
}

class Film {
  - title: String
  - yearOfRelease: Integer
  - genre: String
  - filmSets: List<FilmSet>
}

class Screenwriter {
  - name: String
  - mostSuccessfulFilm: String
  - screenplays: List<Screenplay>
}

class Screenplay {
  - title: String
  - version: Integer
  - date: Date
  - numberOfScenes: Integer
  - plot: String
  - basis: String
  - novel: Novel or Concept
  - film: Film
}

class Novel {
  - title: String
  - author: String
}

class Concept {
  - description: String
}

Employee <|-- CreativeEmployee
CreativeEmployee <|-- Director
CreativeEmployee <|-- Actor
Employee <|-- Technician

FilmSet "0..*" -- "1..*" Film: uses
Film "1..*" -- "0..*" FilmSet: shotAt

Screenwriter "1" -- "0..*" Screenplay: writes
Screenplay "1" -- "1" Film: basedOn
Screenplay "1" -- "0..*" Novel: basedOnNovel
Screenplay "1" -- "0..*" Concept: basedOnConcept

note right of Screenplay
  basis can be either "novel" or "concept"
end note

@enduml

---

### ✅ Summary of Classes and Relationships:

- **Employee**: Base class for all employees.
- **CreativeEmployee**: Subclass of `Employee`, including `Director` and `Actor`.
- **Director**: Has an assistant's name and can be an Oscar winner.
- **Actor**: Has education details and can be an Oscar winner.
- **Technician**: Has a field of activity.
- **FilmSet**: Has a location and is used by multiple films.
- **Film**: Has title, release year, genre, and is shot at multiple film sets.
- **Screenwriter**: Creates screenplays and has a most successful film.
- **Screenplay**: Based on a novel or concept, linked to a film and a screenwriter.
- **Novel**: Title and author.
- **Concept**: Description (optional).

